CAPE Town City have confirmed that Abbubaker Mobara has extended his stay with the club. Mobara joined The Citizens at the start of the 2019-20 season on a free transfer from Orlando Pirates following his unsuccessful stint with the Buccaneers. "The club is delighted to confirm that we have exercised the option to extend the contract of defender Abbubaker Mobara. He signs until June 2023." the club said in a brief statement. ?? | The club is delighted to confirm that we have exercised the option to extend the contract of defender Abbubaker Mobara. He signs until June 2023 ???#iamCityFC pic.twitter.com/pTZf2t7vaV   